        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 24 at 11:33PM CDT until April 25 at 12:15AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
North central Gray County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southwestern Roberts County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 1215 AM CDT.

* At 1132 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles west of
Codman, or 8 miles northeast of Pampa, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

* Locations impacted include...
Codman.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
